version: 17.0.2So `react-router-dom-v5-compat` has a nested `react-router@6.30.0` which itself has a nested `react@17.0.2`. This creates duplicate React instances causing the "Invalid hook call" error in tests. The root cause is likely the `@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk` pulling in `react@^17.0.1` which gets hoisted or nested improperly.

