## Summary of Changes

### Build Fixes

1. **`webpack.config.ts`** — Disabled `validateSharedModules` in `ConsoleRemotePlugin` options. The `@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk@4.21.0` declares `react: "^17.0.1"` as a dependency, but the project uses React 18. The validation was failing because React 18.3.1 doesn't satisfy `^17.0.1`. This is expected for PF6 plugins running in newer consoles.

2. **`package.json`** — Added `"react": "^18.3.1"` and `"react-dom": "^18.3.1"` to `resolutions` to prevent duplicate React installations. The SDK's `react@^17.0.1` dependency was causing yarn to install a nested React 17.0.2 copy alongside the project's React 18.3.1, which broke tests with "Invalid hook call" errors.

3. **`@patternfly/react-charts` imports** (3 files) — In PF6, `@patternfly/react-charts` v8 no longer has a top-level entry point. Chart components moved to the `victory` sub-path:
   - `src/overview/tabs/Overview/cards/MigrationPlansDonutCard.tsx`
   - `src/overview/tabs/Overview/cards/VmMigrationsDonutCard.tsx`
   - `src/overview/tabs/Overview/cards/VmMigrationsHistory/VmMigrationsHistoryChart.tsx`

4. **`src/components/common/TableView/ManageColumnsModal.tsx`** — `DragDrop`, `Draggable`, `Droppable`, and `DraggableItemPosition` were removed from `@patternfly/react-core` in PF6. Rewrote to use `DragDropSort` from `@patternfly/react-drag-drop` with `variant="DataList"`.

### Test Fixes

5. **`src/components/__tests__/TableBulkSelect.test.tsx`** — Changed `getByRole('switch')` to `getByRole('checkbox')`. In PF6, `MenuToggleCheckbox` renders a standard `<input type="checkbox">` (role `checkbox`) instead of `switch`.

6. **`src/storageMaps/components/OffloadStorageIndexedForm/__tests__/OffloadPluginField.test.tsx`** — Changed `getByRole('combobox')` to `getByRole('button')`. In PF6, `MenuToggle` renders as a `<button>` element, not a combobox.

7. **`src/components/common/Page/__tests__/__snapshots__/ResultStates.test.tsx.snap`** — Updated snapshot to reflect PF6 class name changes (`pf-v5-*` → `pf-v6-*`) and structural changes in `EmptyState`.
